<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-660-543  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 660 543.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  Nov 19 1990 n327 p6(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Users blast Bell plans.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Killette, Kathleen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Users have asked the Federal Communications Commission (FCC) toinitiate a wide investigation of switching and networkarchitectures to be deployed by the Bell regional holdingcompanies by 1994.andP;  At issue is the development of the intelligentnetwork and the degree of influence regulators and customers willhave in that development.andP;  Evolution of the public switchednetwork is at a critical juncture, according to user groups.andP;  TheFCC will be reluctant to order the Bell regionals to replaceswitches and network architecture if they have not beensufficiently amortized.andP;  Bell officials insist they are unbundlingtheir networks as much as possible and that they have given usersand providers every chance to influence the development ofadvanced intelligent networks.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     InvestigationsBell Regional Holding CompaniesLocal Area NetworksUnited States. Federal Communications CommissionCommunications EquipmentUser Groups.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>